A former Attorney General has called for the Prime Minister to resign. Jeremy Wright becomes the latest Conservative MP to tell Boris Johnson to quit following the partygate scandal. In a lengthy statement, running to 2,303 words, published on his website, he wrote: ‘I fear that these events have done real and lasting damage to the reputation not just of this Government but to the institutions and authority of Government more generally.’ There was some confusion about the intervention briefly disappearing from his website, but a spokesperson confirmed to Metro.co.uk that it is genuine and it has since reappeared. The statement continued: ‘I have therefore, with regret, concluded that, for the good of this and future Governments, the Prime Minister should resign.’ This is a breaking news story, more to follow soon… Check back shortly for further updates. Got a story? Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. Or you can submit your videos and pictures here. For more stories like this, check our news page. Follow Metro.co.uk on Twitter and Facebook for the latest news updates. You can now also get Metro.co.uk articles sent straight to your device. Sign up for our daily push alerts here.